				-
					-
						Agni inflamed with fuel in my song I sing, pure, Cleanser, steadlast, set
						in tront at sacrifice.
					-
					-
						Wise Jatavedas we implore with prayers for bliss the Priest, the holy
						Singer, bounteous, void of guile.
					-
				-
					Mandala 6: Hymn 15: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Men, Agni, in each age have made thee, Deathiess One, their envoy,
						offering-bearer, guard adorable.
					-
					-
