				-
					-
						These gladdening drops, O Indra, Self-sustainer, quaffed shall augment thee
						in thy mighty splendour.
					-
					-
						Yea, let the cheering drops delight thee greatly, great, perfect, strong,
						powerful, all-subduing.
					-
				-
					Mandala 6: Hymn 17: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Gladdened whereby, bursting the firm enclosures, thou gavest splendour to
						the Sun and Morning.
					-
					-
						The mighty rock that compassed in the cattle, ne'er moved, thou shookest
						from its seat, O Indra.
					-
				-
					Mandala 6: Hymn 17: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Thou with thy wisdom, power, and works of wonder, hast stored the ripe milk
						in the raw cows' udders
					-
					-
						Unbarred the firm doors for the kine of Morning, and, with the Angirases,
